<TITLE> Joypurhat SP retired over graft </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 8 (bdnews24.com) Joypurhat's superintendent of police AKM Masudul Alam has been sent into forced retirement over allegations about irregularities in recruitment and corruption. He was forced to retire according to a decision of the home ministry of June 5. Before that, on June 3, he was stripped of his official powers and was posted at the headquarters The inspector general of police Nur Mohammad confirmed to bdnews24.com the action taken by the authorities . Earlier, around midday, Masudul told journalists about the decision while leaving Joypurhat for his home. He said he was withdrawn from Joypurhat SP's office and attached to the police headquarters through an order of the home ministry on June 3. He was then forced to retire on June 5. Masudul passed the 15th Bangladesh Civil Service examinations and joined as assistant superintendent of police on Apr 18, 1995. He is the son of late policeman Abdul Mannan of Parampasha of Jhalakathi's Swarupkathi. A number of Joypurhat police officials, wishing not to be named, told bdnews24.com that there were a number of allegations against Masudul for irregularities and corruption during the appointment of constables. He is alleged to have destroyed evidence relating to the murder of former finance minister Shah AMS Kibria and of the grenade attack of Aug 21, 2004 at a rally of Awami League that was being addressed by then opposition chief Sheikh Hasina, now prime minister. Masudul said, "Sixteen constables were appointed under my supervision during the former caretaker government's tenure. Three were to be appointed from the freedom fighter quota. "But since there were no quota applicants, three were recruited from among general candidates." "Other than this, I was on duty in Netrakona during the Kibria killing. And I was under medical tests as part of preparations to go on a peacekeeping mission during the Aug 21 grenade attack." "So the punishment is nothing except political enmity and departmental conspiracy." The district's additional SP Mashrukur Rahman Khalid, ASP Noor Alam, Sadar police chief Abu Hena Mostafa Kamal and others were present when Alam left his residence. bdnews24.com/
